<item>
            <title>[LU-5840] Should Null pointer occurrence in mdc_unpack_acl throw a warning</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5840</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A possible null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl was reported and fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4787&quot; title=&quot;OOPS from null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5150&quot; title=&quot;NULL pointer dereference in posix_acl_valid() under mdc_get_lustre_md()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. While the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5150&quot; title=&quot;NULL pointer dereference in posix_acl_valid() under mdc_get_lustre_md()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; just prevents the dereference, the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4787&quot; title=&quot;OOPS from null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in addition throws a warning. As explained in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5150&quot; title=&quot;NULL pointer dereference in posix_acl_valid() under mdc_get_lustre_md()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I have indications that this NULL pointer occurence can indicate some FS corruption and is thus worthwhile to notice. Working with the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4787&quot; title=&quot;OOPS from null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for more than half a year now, judging from our experience on multiple clusters, the issue occurs rarely (actually just on one cluster so far) so I don&apos;t  see a danger of log flooding.&lt;br/&gt;
I therefore propose to use the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4787&quot; title=&quot;OOPS from null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>At least ZFS based MGS/MDS/OSS</environment>
